oviding centralized smart home automation and integration.\\nRuns as a VM on Proxmox, with integrations to MQTT, Frigate, amcrest2mqtt, and other homelab services.\\nAccess is internal-only via `homeassistant.cruver.network` and ZeroTier VPN.\\n\\n** Deployment\\n- **Host:* Proxmox (1U Supermicro server)\\n- **Type:** Virtual Machine (VM)\\n- **Networking:** Runs in IoT VLAN (with access to Kubernetes cluster and other automation services)\\n- **Access:** HTTPS through OPNsense + HAProxy, ZeroTier for remote access\\n\\n** Integrations\\n- **MQTT** – backbone for IoT device communication\\n- **Frigate** – camera recording (triggered by MQTT from amcrest2mqtt)\\n- **amcrest2mqtt** – camera events, person/motion detection via MQTT\\n- **Zerotier** – remote secure access\\n- [[id:c66dcb2a-7b86-11f0-9347-938641e9519d][Node Red]]\\n\\n** Automations\\n- Camera events → MQTT → Frigate recording triggers\\n- Garage door opener (Shelly 1 relay + reed switch) integration\\n- Presence detection via VLAN/device state\\n- Voice assistant experimentation (local LLMs + TTS/STT)\\n\\n** Usage\\n- Central control for smart home devices\\n- Integration hub between IoT hardware, cameras, and Kubernetes-hosted services\\n- Testing ground for advanced automations (voice, AI, n8n workflows)\\n\\n** Notes\\n- Frigate detection is disabled; HA relies on MQTT events for efficiency\\n- Certificates managed via OPNsense + HAProxy (HTTP disabled once HTTPS available)\\n- VMs are low-traffic; CPU overcommitment on Proxmox is acceptable\\n\",\"properties\":{\"embedding\":\"0.406776 1.115247 -3.111906 -0.128874 0.247930 -0.876756 -0.165258 0.102561 1.215844 -1.098527 -0.680048 0.934269 1.068659 0.653508 -0.167065 -0.241101 0.110237 1.037355 -0.997037 -0.741328 0.502527 -0.763643 -1.462386 -0.262190 1.757310 1.155311 -0.415199 -0.168708 0.164882 -0.156414 0.484660 -0.600746 -0.706870 -0.372598 -0.633763 -0.271606 1.306801 0.077270 -0.877417 0.826855 -0.064656 -0.993157 0.153047 -0.885128 0.262482