zing notes in the org-roam knowledge management system. The three-property system provides powerful organization without maintenance overhead.\n\n* Core Properties\n\n** :DOMAIN: (Subject Classification)\n\n/Purpose:/ Categorizes notes by subject matter or area of focus\n\n*** Values\n- =homelab= :: Self-hosted infrastructure, servers, networking, automation\n- =3d-printing= :: Additive manufacturing, printers, filaments, models, troubleshooting\n- =halloween= :: Seasonal decorations, props, effects, displays\n- =music= :: Instruments, recording, theory, performance, audio equipment\n- =software= :: Programming, development tools, applications, coding projects\n- =hardware= :: Electronics, components, devices, specifications\n- =telos= :: Purpose, goals, philosophy, life direction, wisdom, personal development\n- =personal= :: Life management, goals, reflections, non-technical content\n- =meta= :: About the knowledge system itself, org-roam configuration, workflows\n\n*** Guidelines\n- Choose the most specific applicable domain\n- Use =meta= for notes about your knowledge system itself\n\n** :NODE-TYPE: (Structural Role)\n\n/Purpose:/ Defines the note\'s function within the knowledge graph structure\n\n*** Values\n- =root= :: High-level entry points into knowledge domains\n  - Domain overviews and "start here" pages\n  - Major topic introductions\n  - Knowledge area maps\n  - /Examples:/ "Homelab Architecture Overview", "3D Printing Knowledge Base"\n\n- =hub= :: Connection and navigation nodes\n  - Primarily links to other notes\n  - Lists, inventories, catalogs\n  - Topic collections and indexes\n  - /Examples:/ "Active Projects", "Hardware Inventory", "Troubleshooting Index"\n\n- =leaf= :: Detailed, specific content nodes\n  - Deep technical information\n  - Specific procedures and how-tos\n  - Detailed analysis or research\n  - Terminal nodes with implementation details\n  - /Examples:/ "Nginx SSL Configuration", "Ender 3 Bed Leveling"\n\n- =bridge= :: Cross-domain connection nodes\n  - Notes that link concepts across different domains\n  - Integration patterns and workflows\n  - Multi-domain projects\n  - /Examples:/ "Home Automation Integration", "3D Printing for Halloween Props"\n\n*** Guidelines\n- Most notes should be =leaf= (detailed content)\n- =hub= notes should be primarily links with minimal content\n- =root= notes provide orientation and overview\n- =bridge= notes explicitly connect different domains\n\n** :CONTENT-TYPE: (Information Classification)\n\n/Purpose:/ Describes the kind of information contained in the note\n\n*** Values\n- =concept= :: Explanatory or definitional content\n  - Theory, principles, background knowledge\n  - "What is X?" or "How does X work?" explanations\n  - /Examples:/ "Docker Container Concepts", "Mesh Bed Leveling Theory"\n\n- =procedure= :: Step-by-step instructions\n  - How-to guides and tutorials\n  - Installation and configuration steps\n  - Troubleshooting workflows\n  - /Examples:/ "Installing Proxmox", "Calibrating E-steps"\n\n- =reference= :: Quick lookup information\n  - Specifications, settings, parameters\n  - Command references and cheat sheets\n  - Standards and conventions\n  - /Examples:/ "Nginx Configuration Options", "Filament Temperature Chart"\n\n- =troubleshooting= :: Problem-solving information\n  - Error symptoms and solutions\n  - Diagnostic procedures\n  - Common issues and fixes\n  - /Examples:/ "Print Quality Issues", "Matrix Federation Problems"\n\n- =analysis= :: Research and investigation results\n  - Comparisons and evaluations\n  - Performance testing results\n  - Decision matrices and trade-offs\n  - /Examples:/ "SLA vs FDM Comparison", "VPN Performance Analysis"\n\n- =log= :: Time-based entries and updates\n  - Project progress notes\n  - Change logs and maintenance records\n  - Event documentation\n  - /Examples:/ "Server Maintenance Log", "Print Farm Status Updates"\n\n- =inventory= :: Lists and catalogs\n  - Hardware and software inventories\n  - Collections and databases\n  - Status tracking lists\n  - /Examples:/ "Hardware Stack Overview", "Filament Inventory"\n\n*** Guidelines\n- Choose based on primary content purpose\n- =inventory= typically pairs with =hub= node-type\n- =procedure= and =troubleshooting= are often =leaf= nodes\n- =concept= can be any node-type depending on scope\n\n* Property Combinations\n\n** Common Patterns\n\n#+begin_example\n# Domain entry point with conceptual overview\n:DOMAIN: homelab\n:NODE-TYPE: root\n:CONTENT-TYPE: concept\n\n# Hardware inventory hub\n:DOMAIN: hardware\n:NODE-TYPE: hub\n:CONTENT-TYPE: inventory\n\n# Detailed technical procedure\n:DOMAIN: 3d-printing\n:NODE-TYPE: leaf\n:CONTENT-TYPE: procedure\n\n# Cross-domain troubleshooting guide\n:DOMAIN: homelab\n:NODE-TYPE: bridge\n:CONTENT-TYPE: troubleshooting\n\n# Reference documentation\n:DOMAIN: software\n:NODE-TYPE: leaf\n:CONTENT-TYPE: reference\n#+end_example\n\n** Logical Pairings\n- *Root + Concept* :: Domain overviews and introductions\n- *Hub + Inventory* :: Lists, catalogs, collections\n- *Leaf + Procedure* :: Detailed how-to guides\n- *Leaf + Reference* :: Lookup tables, specifications\n- *Bridge + Analysis* :: Cross-domain comparisons\n- *Any + Troubleshooting* :: Problem-solving content\n\n** Validation Rules\n- All notes MUST have all three properties\n- Only one value per property (no comma-separated lists)\n- Values must match exactly (case-sensitive)\n- No custom values without updating this specification\n\n* Migration Guidelines\n\n** From Existing Properties\n- =:STATUS: idea|active|completed= → Remove (project-oriented)\n- =:PRIORITY: high|medium|low= → Remove (project-oriented)\n- =:CONFIDENCE: high|medium|low= → Remove (maintenance overhead)\n- Existing =:TYPE:= values → Remap to =:NODE-TYPE:= (structural) and =:CONTENT-TYPE:= (informational)\n- Existing =:DOMAIN:= values → Mostly keep, some refinement needed\n\n** Auto-Classification Hints\n- *Root detection* :: Few incoming links, many outgoing links, broad titles\n- *Hub detection* :: Many incoming links, many outgoing links, list-like content\n- *Leaf detection* :: Many incoming links, few outgoing links, detailed content\n- *Bridge detection* :: Links across multiple domains\n- *Content-type detection* :: Analyze content patterns (steps = procedure, definitions = concept, etc.)\n\n* Integration with Tools\n\n** org-roam-ui Visualization\n- Could color-code by NODE-TYPE (roots=blue, hubs=green, leaves=gray, bridges=orange)\n- Filter by DOMAIN for focused views\n- Shape nodes by CONTENT-TYPE (circles=concept, squares=procedure, diamonds=reference)\n- Size nodes by connection count or recent activity\n\n** n8n Workflow Integration\n- Search can filter by properties: "show me homelab procedures"\n- Note creation can auto-suggest NODE-TYPE and CONTENT-TYPE based on content analysis\n- Property-based search: "find all troubleshooting content" or "show hub nodes"\n\n** Search and Discovery\n- "What procedures do I have for 3d-printing?"\n- "Show me all bridge notes to find cross-domain opportunities"\n- "List all troubleshooting notes for review"\n- "Find concept notes that could become root nodes"\n- "Show me inventory hubs to update"\n\n* Future Extensions\n\n** Additional Properties (if needed)\n- =:UPDATED:= :: Last significant content change (YYYY-MM-DD)\n- =:REVIEWED:= :: Last time information was verified (YYYY-MM-DD)\n- =:SOURCE:= :: Where information came from (personal|official|community)\n- =:VERIFIED:= :: Has been tested/confirmed working (yes|no)\n\n** Validation\n- Create validation functions to check property consistency\n- Automated reports on taxonomy compliance\n- Suggestions for notes missing properties\n\n* Implementation Notes\n\n** Property Block Format\n#+begin_example\n:PROPERTIES:\n:ID: 1755213279\n:DOMAIN: homelab\n:NODE-TYPE: leaf\n:CONTENT-TYPE: procedure\n:END:\n#+title: Note Title\n#+end_example\n\n** Emacs Integration\n- Add to org-roam capture templates\n- Create helper functions for property validation\n- Build search functions that leverage the taxonomy\n\nThis taxonomy provides structure while remaining flexible for future growth. The combination of domain knowledge, structural role, and content type gives you multiple dimensions for organizing and finding information without maintenance overhead.\n', 'properties': {'embedding': '0.651152 0.081019 -2.543670 -0.567900 1.306725 -0.844238 0.278111 0.226457 0.734792 -1.140219 0.195329 -0.042596 1.463241 0.609105 -0.550623 -0.742509 -0.553392 -0.849253 0.132610 0.857159 0.082829 -0.604855 -0.331971 -0.960082 0.289974 0.721067 -0.059829 -0.420373 -0.263516 0.481854 0.111609 -0.345854 0.144841 0.189637 -0.492347 -0.420930 0.917711 0.554929 -0.333179 1.370279 0.447038 -0.036231 -0.796517 -0.660000 0.439994 0.295232 0.874317 -0.510344 0.975081 -0.261267 -0.046506 0.237375 0.123205 0.469789 1.135949 0.265560 0.228363 0.517455 0.804206 -1.050471 0.945924 2.057196 -0.093562 1.372270 0.927273 0.071131 -0.475914 0.718409 -0.442174 -0.575719 0.417418 -0.211780 0.382248 1.075693 -0.817049 0.333991 0.015631 -0.036778 -0.059249 0.344966 0.197384 0.390094 1.172581 -0.466252 -0.003620 -0.062156 -0.686794 -0.492300 -0.509988 1.330414 0.537471 0.595649 -0.166652 -0.013625 -0.573360 0.590598 -0.097869 0.249659 -0.623793 -0.871922 -0.046984 -0.710021 0.270943 0.416560 -0.610483 0.819280 -0.087630 0.155780 -0.293084 0.119331 -0.277666 0.682989 -0.308383 0.581226 0.021855 -0.618024 2.120808 -0.425103 0.053116 0.735120 -0.033728 0.144072 -0.039096 0.396995 0.262353 -0.366438 0.106798 -0.282807 0.152725 -0.438484 -0.577463 -0.252829 -0.377653 0.622608 0.763616 1.105934 -0.324196 -0.262748 -0.160538 -0.362926 0.235958 -0.721151 -0.132513 0.555979 0.437407 -0.715718 0.673663 -0.437709 -0.398214 0.109556 0.257370 0.145930 -0.124184 -0.131134 0.376998 -0.840999 -0.557017 -0.186927 0.831722 0.387898 0.245621 -0.146501 -1.168600 0.349482 0.215039 -0.522571 -0.453251 0.569944 0.433431 0.794972 -1.179337 -0.696456 0.2330